notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Some more damaged folios restored on modern paper.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 35 41; written lines: 35 41; Uniform layout. Initial words and chapter titles present. Catchwords on every verso.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 13 December 1879: inscribed, folio [188v].
